{"type":"step-attempt","step":"code-review","sessionId":"082787cf-60a1-4c36-9fc1-017522f94fa1","outcome":{"verdict":"approved","findingsPath":"specrunner/changes/bulk-approval/review-feedback-001.md","error":null,"toolResult":{"ok":true,"approved":true,"findings":[{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/__tests__/usecases/bulkApprove.test.ts","title":"TC-001/TC-002 (must unit tests) are static analysis only — partial-success runtime behavior untested","rationale":"TC-001 ('3件の pending 申請を一括承認する') and TC-002 ('2件目が失敗しても1件目と3件目は承認される') are classified as must/unit in test-cases.md, but bulkApprove.test.ts only checks for the presence of a for-loop and results property in the source. The actual partial-success behavior — that one failure does not stop other items — is not verified at runtime. approveRequest could be mocked to return ok:false for one ID to confirm the loop continues."},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/app/(dashboard)/requests/page.tsx","title":"bulkApproveAction.bind(null) is non-idiomatic — no arguments to pre-bind","rationale":"bulkApproveAction.bind(null) creates a new function reference with this=null but pre-binds no arguments, making it functionally identical to passing bulkApproveAction directly. In Next.js App Router, .bind(null, serverSideArg) is the convention for closing over server-side data before passing a Server Action to a Client Component. When there is no data to pre-bind, passing the action directly is cleaner and avoids implying a non-existent binding intent.","line":40},{"severity":"low","resolution":"fixable","file":"src/infrastructure/repositories/userRepository.ts","title":"Out-of-scope duplicate findByOrganization removal included in PR diff","rationale":"The 17 deleted lines remove an older duplicate findByOrganization function (using .select() without explicit column projection) that predates this feature. The cleanup is correct and harmless, but it is unrelated to bulk-approval and adds noise to the PR diff. Future PRs should isolate unrelated cleanup into separate commits.","origin":"scope"}],"observations":[{"severity":"low","file":"src/app/actions/requests.ts","title":"Rate limiting implemented as 20-item cap only — no dedicated rate-limit infrastructure","rationale":"spec-review finding #2 (MEDIUM) noted that the rate limiting requirement in request.md ('requestIds.length 分のクォータを消費') has no infrastructure backing. The implementation correctly uses the 20-item limit as the approved fallback, but no actual per-user quota is tracked. This was accepted in spec-review and is recorded here for traceability."},{"severity":"low","file":"src/app/actions/requests.ts","title":"requestIds elements validated as z.string() only, not z.string().uuid()","rationale":"spec-review finding #1 (MEDIUM) recommended z.string().uuid() for requestId elements to maintain defensive consistency with the existing UUID_RE guard on idempotency keys. The implementation uses z.string() as specified in tasks.md. Recorded for traceability; no code change required."}]},"followUpAttempts":1,"transientRetryAttempts":0},"startedAt":"2026-06-18T03:50:08.970Z","endedAt":"2026-06-18T03:56:28.458Z"}
